  "prompt": "Why do I see the same questions in my Quora feed even if I refresh?",
  "response": "Seeing the same questions in your Quora feed after refreshing can be attributed to a few factors:\n\n1. **Algorithmic Ranking**: Quora uses an algorithm to curate your feed based on your interests, interactions, and the type of content you engage with. If certain topics or questions align with your preferences, they may keep appearing.\n\n2. **Limited Content**: Depending on the topics you follow and the current activity on the platform, there may be a limited number of new questions being posted, leading to repetition.\n\n3. **Personalized Content**: Quora aims to show you content that it believes you'll find relevant. If your interactions with certain questions or topics are high, the algorithm might prioritize those questions in your feed.\n\n4. **Recent Activity**: If you refresh shortly after your last visit, the new content may not have populated yet, resulting in the same posts being displayed.\n\n5. **Account Settings**: Your feed could reflect changes in your settings or interests if you've adjusted what topics you follow, leading to some questions reappearing.\n\nIf you're looking for more variety, consider exploring new topics, unfollowing some subjects, or engaging with different content to help diversify the questions you see.",
